1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:37,357 --> 00:01:39,316
My company is preparing to sue me.

3
00:01:42,236 --> 00:01:43,997
Why aren't you surprised at all?

4
00:01:44,277 --> 00:01:45,236
It was expected.

5
00:01:46,917 --> 00:01:48,236
You've already resigned.

6
00:01:48,877 --> 00:01:51,717
If GST wants to pursue this,
suing you is their only option.

7
00:01:54,196 --> 00:01:55,956
I'm just a bit emotional.

8
00:01:56,637 --> 00:01:59,877
The company I've loyally served
for ten years

9
00:02:00,277 --> 00:02:02,637
is now taking me to court.

10
00:02:04,357 --> 00:02:07,036
The day Xu's suspension notice came out,

11
00:02:07,036 --> 00:02:09,437
the company cleared out his office.

12
00:02:09,437 --> 00:02:10,877
Like a raid.

13
00:02:11,476 --> 00:02:13,677
I expect my office
will get the same treatment.

14
00:02:15,516 --> 00:02:16,796
In the corporate world,

15
00:02:17,157 --> 00:02:18,476
life and death are commonplace.

16
00:02:21,837 --> 00:02:25,076
I just find it heartless that a company

17
00:02:25,076 --> 00:02:26,997
I've worked so hard for can turn on me

18
00:02:27,157 --> 00:02:28,117
so quickly.

19
00:02:30,277 --> 00:02:32,516
Have you heard of the Ship of Theseus?

20
00:02:33,196 --> 00:02:34,196
It's a ship.

21
00:02:34,717 --> 00:02:36,277
From the day it was launched,

22
00:02:37,356 --> 00:02:39,877
when a plank rots,
it gets replaced with a new one.

23
00:02:40,157 --> 00:02:42,277
When a part breaks,
it gets replaced with a new part.

24
00:02:43,157 --> 00:02:44,516
After many years,

25
00:02:44,636 --> 00:02:46,437
every plank and part of the entire ship

26
00:02:46,437 --> 00:02:47,636
is replaced with new ones.

27
00:02:48,356 --> 00:02:50,717
Would you say it's still the same ship?

28
00:02:51,877 --> 00:02:53,316
Probably not.

29
00:02:54,437 --> 00:02:55,356
The answer matters not.

30
00:02:55,997 --> 00:02:57,397
The point is

31
00:02:57,796 --> 00:02:59,437
that a company is like a ship.

32
00:03:00,516 --> 00:03:02,076
No matter who comes or goes,

33
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:04,877
even if every single person is replaced,

34
00:03:05,237 --> 00:03:07,076
it can still sail forward.

35
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,557
It's always people
who have feelings for the ship.

36
00:03:10,356 --> 00:03:11,796
When have you ever heard

37
00:03:12,437 --> 00:03:14,157
of a ship having feelings for people?

38
00:03:20,356 --> 00:03:22,596
HR expert,

39
00:03:25,157 --> 00:03:26,636
I'm hungry.

40
00:03:28,356 --> 00:03:29,036
Okay.

41
00:03:29,316 --> 00:03:30,076
I'm hungry.

42
00:03:30,356 --> 00:03:31,237
Alright.

43
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:40,040
(Everyone has something they fear.)

44
00:03:42,999 --> 00:03:47,112
=Episode 5=
(Out of Control)

45
00:04:27,997 --> 00:04:28,968
Who is this?

46
00:04:30,917 --> 00:04:32,076
A junior analyst.

47
00:04:32,316 --> 00:04:33,608
(My first time golfing)
Qiao Hailun?

48
00:04:33,608 --> 00:04:34,316
(So tired I could drop dead,
but still very happy)

49
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:35,557
Her name is quite nice.

50
00:04:36,156 --> 00:04:37,396
She's also quite pretty.

51
00:04:38,636 --> 00:04:40,357
Just has a bit of a tough fate.

52
00:04:40,716 --> 00:04:42,237
Our company will soon downsize.

53
00:04:42,956 --> 00:04:44,437
She'll likely be laid off soon.

54
00:04:44,677 --> 00:04:45,316
Why?

55
00:04:46,156 --> 00:04:47,117
Worst performance?

56
00:04:47,677 --> 00:04:50,477
Because the company has its standards.

57
00:04:52,076 --> 00:04:52,997
How sad.

58
00:04:53,396 --> 00:04:54,716
Does she know?

59
00:04:55,237 --> 00:04:56,156
Not yet.

60
00:04:58,956 --> 00:05:00,956
Did you play golf with Barry today?

61
00:05:01,117 --> 00:05:02,076
You took her along?

62
00:05:02,396 --> 00:05:03,156
Yeah.

63
00:05:03,557 --> 00:05:04,516
He brought his girl.

64
00:05:04,516 --> 00:05:05,836
I couldn't exactly bring a guy.

65
00:05:06,677 --> 00:05:07,797
Danning told you, right?

66
00:05:09,156 --> 00:05:10,797
I call this 'courtesy before force.'

67
00:05:11,117 --> 00:05:12,156
Today was the courtesy.

68
00:05:12,557 --> 00:05:13,797
Next comes the force.

69
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:16,716
What are you planning to do?

70
00:05:17,237 --> 00:05:18,956
I'm going to take on
your company's project.

71
00:05:20,156 --> 00:05:21,677
That means doing a background check.

72
00:05:22,396 --> 00:05:23,997
Your company has so many distributors.

73
00:05:24,516 --> 00:05:27,037
I believe
I will find evidence of kickbacks.

74
00:05:27,997 --> 00:05:30,636
So you're giving up on GST as a client?

75
00:05:30,836 --> 00:05:32,797
GST is about to come after my wife.

76
00:05:33,276 --> 00:05:34,557
Why do I want them as a client?

77
00:05:42,477 --> 00:05:44,037
I like hearing you say that.

78
00:05:47,037 --> 00:05:49,396
But you don't need to talk to them yet.

79
00:05:50,156 --> 00:05:51,797
Wait until I'm truly stuck.

80
00:05:52,557 --> 00:05:53,437
Then you step in.

81
00:05:55,677 --> 00:05:56,836
Given what you said,

82
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:58,357
you've got backup plans?

83
00:05:59,156 --> 00:06:00,797
I've got these moves too.

84
00:06:01,037 --> 00:06:02,276
You'll need it.

85
00:06:34,312 --> 00:06:35,557
Hello, Ms. Qi?

86
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:39,076
Today at 3 PM,
the 24th-floor conference room awaits.

87
00:06:40,396 --> 00:06:42,156
We have some matters
to discuss with you.

88
00:06:45,992 --> 00:06:47,156
Okay.

89
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,797
See you this afternoon.

90
00:06:55,156 --> 00:06:56,997
Qi Youlan wants to meet me
at 3 PM today.

91
00:07:00,956 --> 00:07:03,037
I'll cancel my afternoon meeting
and go with you.

92
00:07:10,557 --> 00:07:11,357
What's on your mind?

93
00:07:13,756 --> 00:07:16,037
About what Qi Youlan might say to me

94
00:07:17,076 --> 00:07:18,237
and what they'll do to me.

95
00:07:18,477 --> 00:07:19,477
Just two points today.

96
00:07:19,917 --> 00:07:22,276
First, Zhao Mei
didn't resign voluntarily.

97
00:07:22,276 --> 00:07:23,437
She was fired by the company.

98
00:07:24,037 --> 00:07:25,716
Whatever it'll be, I'll be with you.

99
00:07:26,037 --> 00:07:26,636
Fear not.

100
00:07:27,357 --> 00:07:30,357
Second, she needs
to publicly apologize to GST.

101
00:07:30,997 --> 00:07:32,357
If she disagrees with either,

102
00:07:33,156 --> 00:07:33,800
we'll sue her.

103
00:07:35,636 --> 00:07:36,997
I'm not afraid of them.

104
00:07:40,117 --> 00:07:41,357
Shame you got involved.

105
00:07:42,557 --> 00:07:45,276
I should have told you beforehand.

106
00:07:46,316 --> 00:07:47,316
Let it not happen again.

107
00:08:33,477 --> 00:08:34,717
- Ms. Qi.
- Ms. Qi.

108
00:08:34,837 --> 00:08:37,036
I didn't expect you two
to come together.

109
00:08:38,197 --> 00:08:38,756
Zhao Mei,

110
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:42,636
your speech at the sales promoter
conference was fantastic.

111
00:08:43,717 --> 00:08:44,877
You honored the company.

112
00:08:45,636 --> 00:08:46,597
Please, have a seat.

113
00:08:47,676 --> 00:08:48,837
Barry wants to say something.

114
00:08:50,664 --> 00:08:52,477
Hi, Zhao Mei.

115
00:08:52,717 --> 00:08:53,477
Hi, Barry.

116
00:08:53,877 --> 00:08:54,756
Hello, Barry.

117
00:08:55,237 --> 00:08:56,436
Dongming, my friend.

118
00:08:57,317 --> 00:08:59,317
You have a truly outstanding wife.

119
00:08:59,796 --> 00:09:01,396
You should be proud of her.

120
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,516
Of course.
I've always been proud of my wife.

121
00:09:05,117 --> 00:09:06,556
I'll always stand by her side.

122
00:09:06,877 --> 00:09:09,997
Thank you for your efforts
to protect the company's reputation.

123
00:09:11,237 --> 00:09:14,597
Your speech at the promoter conference
was very well received.

124
00:09:14,837 --> 00:09:15,717
Not just by me,

125
00:09:16,117 --> 00:09:18,036
but also by the Asia-Pacific office.

126
00:09:19,276 --> 00:09:21,477
As it turns out, whole brilliance.

127
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:24,717
The crisis PR strategy
was a great success.

128
00:09:25,556 --> 00:09:26,837
I'm on a business trip tomorrow.

129
00:09:27,717 --> 00:09:29,512
- Return to the office...
- (I'm smiling,)

130
00:09:30,317 --> 00:09:32,197
(but I'm not happy at all inside.)

131
00:09:33,077 --> 00:09:34,472
(It was clearly a dead end.)

132
00:09:34,472 --> 00:09:34,916
Thank you.

133
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:37,317
(Yet it did
a complete 180-degree turnaround.)

134
00:09:38,117 --> 00:09:39,957
(I don't know
how Zhao Mei pulled it off.)

135
00:09:40,477 --> 00:09:43,396
(But I know this victory
has nothing to do with me.)

136
00:09:44,197 --> 00:09:45,916
(And that's precisely
the part I hate most)

137
00:09:46,436 --> 00:09:47,916
(about this whole thing.)

138
00:09:48,197 --> 00:09:49,597
Miguel and I both believe

139
00:09:49,957 --> 00:09:52,357
(Wang Shengdong, GST Asia-Pacific VP)
Your initiative in admitting the mistake

140
00:09:52,556 --> 00:09:53,357
was very courageous.

141
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,436
Bowing and apologizing to the promoters

142
00:09:55,877 --> 00:09:59,197
further demonstrates GST's magnanimity.

143
00:09:59,837 --> 00:10:03,516
I've also noticed public perception
of our company is improving.

144
00:10:04,197 --> 00:10:07,837
Was this a pre-arranged PR plan?

145
00:10:10,436 --> 00:10:11,396
You saw through it.

146
00:10:12,556 --> 00:10:13,717
It was indeed arranged.

147
00:10:14,357 --> 00:10:15,597
But it wasn't a PR plan.

148
00:10:16,676 --> 00:10:19,837
Actually, I feel really sorry
about the whole

149
00:10:19,837 --> 00:10:21,036
sexual harassment thing.

150
00:10:21,276 --> 00:10:25,477
And personally, I do think
we owe these girls some apology.

151
00:10:25,636 --> 00:10:26,477
Well said.

152
00:10:26,877 --> 00:10:32,117
Before founding GST, our chairman
was a beer promoter himself.

153
00:10:33,036 --> 00:10:35,436
It's the efforts of countless promoters

154
00:10:35,837 --> 00:10:37,997
that built GST into what it is today.

155
00:10:38,636 --> 00:10:41,156
This is a commendable crisis PR effort.

156
00:10:41,756 --> 00:10:43,556
I'll email headquarters

157
00:10:43,957 --> 00:10:46,036
to recommend commendation
for the China division.

158
00:10:48,276 --> 00:10:49,357
Thank you so much.

159
00:10:51,796 --> 00:10:53,357
What's Asia-Pacific playing at?

160
00:10:54,597 --> 00:10:57,477
Didn't Wang Shengdong always
want to embarrass our China division?

161
00:10:57,477 --> 00:10:58,997
Now he's praising us

162
00:10:58,997 --> 00:11:01,957
and pushing for recognition?

163
00:11:02,357 --> 00:11:03,516
There are two reasons.

164
00:11:04,717 --> 00:11:08,436
First, he wants to use this to spite me.

165
00:11:08,957 --> 00:11:11,436
Second, the global internal audit
is about to start.

166
00:11:12,717 --> 00:11:14,436
He wants to find a few loose cannons

167
00:11:15,156 --> 00:11:16,756
as leverage points for the audit.

168
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:18,357
Then we should fire Zhao Mei.

169
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:19,237
No.

170
00:11:20,317 --> 00:11:21,197
We can't fire her.

171
00:11:21,796 --> 00:11:24,156
The Asia-Pacific office
has already set the tone.

172
00:11:24,477 --> 00:11:26,516
It's us actively admitting our mistakes.

173
00:11:27,077 --> 00:11:29,117
Zhao Mei will become a model employee

174
00:11:29,396 --> 00:11:30,436
for being brave

175
00:11:30,436 --> 00:11:32,237
to face mistakes, admit them,

176
00:11:32,997 --> 00:11:34,276
and apologize to the staff.

177
00:11:35,197 --> 00:11:37,156
Our board
will always like this kind of thing.

178
00:11:37,237 --> 00:11:38,396
Of being all a saint,

179
00:11:38,472 --> 00:11:39,636
like a holy figure of legend.

180
00:11:39,837 --> 00:11:40,636
By the way,

181
00:11:41,676 --> 00:11:42,957
I only learned today

182
00:11:42,957 --> 00:11:46,837
that our chairman used to be a promoter.

183
00:11:47,756 --> 00:11:48,396
I understand.

184
00:11:48,997 --> 00:11:51,036
I'll do my best to keep Zhao Mei.

185
00:11:51,636 --> 00:11:55,237
By the way, who's the auditor
Asia-Pacific is sending this time?

186
00:11:56,877 --> 00:11:57,556
Don't know.

187
00:11:58,796 --> 00:11:59,756
An enemy, regardless.

188
00:12:02,837 --> 00:12:04,276
Mr. Gao, Ms. Qi is waiting for you.

189
00:12:13,717 --> 00:12:14,237
Zhao Mei.

190
00:12:14,436 --> 00:12:14,997
Jiawei,

191
00:12:16,197 --> 00:12:17,396
thank you so much this time.

192
00:12:17,396 --> 00:12:18,317
You were a huge help.

193
00:12:18,317 --> 00:12:19,276
It was nothing.

194
00:12:20,477 --> 00:12:21,357
Let me introduce him.

195
00:12:21,357 --> 00:12:23,077
This is my husband, Li Dongming.

196
00:12:23,237 --> 00:12:25,317
(Gao Jiawei, VP Assistant, Head of Internal Audit)
This is my former colleague, Gao Jiawei.

197
00:12:25,436 --> 00:12:27,556
He's now
the Asia-Pacific VP's assistant.

198
00:12:28,117 --> 00:12:28,837
Pleasure.

199
00:12:28,997 --> 00:12:29,837
Hello.

200
00:12:30,117 --> 00:12:31,117
Zhao Mei mentioned you.

201
00:12:32,197 --> 00:12:34,117
Nice to finally meet him in person.

202
00:12:36,396 --> 00:12:37,396
I'm meeting with Ms. Qi.

203
00:12:37,396 --> 00:12:38,117
I'm running late.

204
00:12:38,197 --> 00:12:38,796
Go ahead.

205
00:12:39,317 --> 00:12:40,717
Mr. Li, see you later then.

206
00:12:42,877 --> 00:12:43,957
Dinner tonight?

207
00:12:43,957 --> 00:12:44,477
Okay.

208
00:13:00,877 --> 00:13:01,796
Are you mad?

209
00:13:04,197 --> 00:13:06,957
Is he the Gao Jiawei
who pursued you before?

210
00:13:07,477 --> 00:13:09,357
That was ages ago.

211
00:13:09,597 --> 00:13:11,036
If I'm not mistaken,

212
00:13:11,597 --> 00:13:14,957
he was the one who convinced
your Asia-Pacific VP to help, right?

213
00:13:15,636 --> 00:13:17,556
You did so much preparation beforehand.

214
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:19,597
But you never once thought to tell me?

215
00:13:20,117 --> 00:13:21,436
Am I that untrustworthy to you?

216
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:22,556
No.

217
00:13:22,997 --> 00:13:25,916
I just didn't expect him
to have that much influence

218
00:13:26,077 --> 00:13:28,597
to get Wang Shengdong
to personally call Barry.

219
00:13:30,197 --> 00:13:32,117
Besides, I wasn't confident
it would work.

220
00:13:32,117 --> 00:13:34,317
I was genuinely prepared to leave GST.

221
00:13:35,756 --> 00:13:37,128
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

222
00:13:37,676 --> 00:13:38,516
Alright.

223
00:13:39,156 --> 00:13:40,396
Forget it. Anyway,

224
00:13:41,156 --> 00:13:41,957
the outcome is good.

225
00:13:42,436 --> 00:13:43,117
Congratulations.

226
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:47,796
So, let's take him out
to dinner tonight.

227
00:13:48,436 --> 00:13:50,156
I have plans tonight. You go.

228
00:13:51,036 --> 00:13:51,816
Easy on the drinks.

229
00:14:04,117 --> 00:14:06,077
(I've always supported
women's independence.)

230
00:14:06,396 --> 00:14:07,357
(Doesn't Zhao Mei know?)

231
00:14:08,916 --> 00:14:11,156
(But why couldn't she tell me
about the whole thing?)

232
00:14:11,957 --> 00:14:13,156
(Am I that untrustworthy?)

233
00:14:14,357 --> 00:14:16,477
(How many more things
is she hiding from me?)

234
00:14:33,997 --> 00:14:34,556
Qiao Hailun,

235
00:14:35,276 --> 00:14:36,837
come with me to a business dinner.

236
00:15:00,717 --> 00:15:04,077
Tao, that black dress
you wore last time.

237
00:15:04,077 --> 00:15:06,597
The really sparkly one.
Where did you buy it?

238
00:15:07,077 --> 00:15:07,912
The mall downstairs?

239
00:15:08,957 --> 00:15:09,997
Yeah, why?

240
00:15:11,197 --> 00:15:11,957
What brand is it?

241
00:15:12,837 --> 00:15:14,156
From the trendy shop downstairs.

242
00:15:14,837 --> 00:15:15,877
What? You want one too?

243
00:15:17,077 --> 00:15:18,317
Their clothes aren't cheap.

244
00:15:18,317 --> 00:15:19,636
Mine cost over five thousand.

245
00:15:20,396 --> 00:15:21,957
I was broke for a month after that.

246
00:15:25,156 --> 00:15:26,556
No, I was just asking.

247
00:15:28,556 --> 00:15:29,077
Go ahead.

248
00:15:33,676 --> 00:15:34,556
Weird.

249
00:15:35,085 --> 00:15:45,096
(Tiande Center)

250
00:16:00,776 --> 00:16:01,396
Sorry, Mr. Li.

251
00:16:01,396 --> 00:16:01,957
I'm late.

252
00:16:03,516 --> 00:16:06,276
Is my outfit okay
to meet the client with you?

253
00:16:07,396 --> 00:16:07,997
It's fine.

254
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,317
The door...

255
00:16:27,516 --> 00:16:29,117
Kangya Group is one of China's

256
00:16:29,556 --> 00:16:31,077
oldest hotel groups.

257
00:16:31,796 --> 00:16:34,357
Though it's decreased recently,
threadbare silk is still silk.

258
00:16:35,556 --> 00:16:37,237
Mr. Tan fell seriously ill last year

259
00:16:37,237 --> 00:16:37,957
and is retiring

260
00:16:37,957 --> 00:16:40,156
and leaving the company
to his only daughter, Tan Min.

261
00:16:40,516 --> 00:16:43,597
That young lady is planning
an overhaul of the company's structure.

262
00:16:44,077 --> 00:16:45,597
This is a strategic project.

263
00:16:46,556 --> 00:16:48,936
I've been negotiating for three months
and made no progress.

264
00:16:49,837 --> 00:16:50,636
Give me a hand.

265
00:16:51,357 --> 00:16:53,676
If you help me land this,
we'll split profits 60-40.

266
00:16:53,676 --> 00:16:55,117
No, how about 50-50?

267
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:56,636
Profits aside,

268
00:16:57,036 --> 00:16:58,357
what makes you think I can

269
00:16:58,357 --> 00:17:00,036
if you couldn't do it in three months?

270
00:17:00,237 --> 00:17:02,357
You're better at charming girls
than I am.

271
00:17:02,436 --> 00:17:03,077
Stop joking.

272
00:17:04,797 --> 00:17:05,557
I'm serious.

273
00:17:06,156 --> 00:17:08,196
You must land this project
for me tonight.

274
00:17:09,557 --> 00:17:10,636
She is quite a looker.

275
00:17:11,016 --> 00:17:12,168
Why not bring her sooner?

276
00:17:12,597 --> 00:17:13,436
Don't think so.

277
00:17:14,117 --> 00:17:14,676
Ms. Tan,

278
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:16,436
what Dongming means is,

279
00:17:16,956 --> 00:17:20,757
don't rush to purge the old guard
so openly right from the start.

280
00:17:22,277 --> 00:17:24,236
It's likely to stir up resistance.

281
00:17:24,757 --> 00:17:26,996
We should move quietly

282
00:17:27,117 --> 00:17:28,236
without shooting

283
00:17:28,476 --> 00:17:30,476
and proceed gradually, right?

284
00:17:34,236 --> 00:17:35,476
To implement staff changes,

285
00:17:35,996 --> 00:17:37,996
the key is for the leader to be patient.

286
00:17:38,636 --> 00:17:40,837
You can't aim
for a major personnel shake-up

287
00:17:41,277 --> 00:17:44,117
while simultaneously trying
to maintain operational stability.

288
00:17:45,077 --> 00:17:46,636
We can formulate a plan to be completed

289
00:17:46,757 --> 00:17:47,797
over three years.

290
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:48,716
Three years?

291
00:17:49,357 --> 00:17:50,676
Three years is too long.

292
00:17:50,676 --> 00:17:52,396
In three years, it'll be way too late.

293
00:17:52,396 --> 00:17:54,837
Those three years
would be divided into three phases.

294
00:17:55,317 --> 00:17:56,156
For the first phase,

295
00:17:56,277 --> 00:17:57,196
don't move anyone.

296
00:17:57,597 --> 00:17:58,877
The focus would be on signaling.

297
00:17:58,877 --> 00:17:59,476
Yes.

298
00:17:59,476 --> 00:18:02,676
Let all employees understand
the urgency of the changes.

299
00:18:03,236 --> 00:18:06,797
You can also identify which employees
are committed to staying long-term.

300
00:18:07,996 --> 00:18:09,608
The second phase is about eliminations.

301
00:18:10,077 --> 00:18:11,196
Middle management, mainly.

302
00:18:11,597 --> 00:18:12,916
It won't cause major harm.

303
00:18:13,797 --> 00:18:15,716
The third phase
targets the top executives.

304
00:18:16,236 --> 00:18:17,317
Like VP-level positions.

305
00:18:17,636 --> 00:18:19,916
By then,
they'll have lost all influence.

306
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:21,396
They can't do anything about you.

307
00:18:21,396 --> 00:18:23,037
But that still takes three years, right?

308
00:18:23,277 --> 00:18:24,117
It's too long.

309
00:18:24,236 --> 00:18:26,156
I want to see results fast.

310
00:18:26,236 --> 00:18:27,236
Okay, no problem.

311
00:18:27,236 --> 00:18:29,156
Ms. Tan, with all due respect,

312
00:18:29,636 --> 00:18:32,077
if you rush into changes recklessly,

313
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:34,996
it'll only create chaos
and unsettle the workforce.

314
00:18:35,436 --> 00:18:37,877
In the end,
those you want removed might stay,

315
00:18:38,037 --> 00:18:39,956
while unintended casualties occur.

316
00:18:40,517 --> 00:18:43,636
I believe if your dad were here today,

317
00:18:43,636 --> 00:18:44,716
he'd agree with us.

318
00:18:44,716 --> 00:18:45,277
Right.

319
00:18:46,396 --> 00:18:47,156
But he's not here.

320
00:18:47,156 --> 00:18:47,996
He's retired.

321
00:18:47,996 --> 00:18:50,277
I'm now the decision-maker at Kangya.

322
00:18:54,517 --> 00:18:55,236
That's right.

323
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:58,196
Well, Ms. Tan, may I say something?

324
00:18:59,077 --> 00:19:00,916
You know Fisherman Mineral Water, right?

325
00:19:01,636 --> 00:19:04,557
Their situation is similar to yours,

326
00:19:04,636 --> 00:19:05,956
also led by young leadership.

327
00:19:06,277 --> 00:19:09,224
We designed
their organizational strategy,

328
00:19:09,224 --> 00:19:10,277
phased over three years.

329
00:19:10,396 --> 00:19:11,597
It was highly successful.

330
00:19:11,797 --> 00:19:13,156
But that's mineral water.

331
00:19:13,156 --> 00:19:14,277
I'm running hotels.

332
00:19:14,277 --> 00:19:15,236
It's different.

333
00:19:17,037 --> 00:19:17,676
Right.

334
00:19:17,757 --> 00:19:19,597
Come on, let's toast first. Let's drink.

335
00:19:20,236 --> 00:19:20,757
Come on.

336
00:19:25,396 --> 00:19:27,597
(Mr. Fan)
(Dongming, have you composed yourself?)

337
00:19:28,037 --> 00:19:30,317
(The company needs the GST project.)

338
00:19:30,396 --> 00:19:31,396
(You need it even more.)

339
00:19:31,396 --> 00:19:32,956
Excuse me. I need to handle something.

340
00:19:33,636 --> 00:19:34,597
No problem. Go ahead.

341
00:19:42,236 --> 00:19:43,837
Come on. Keep those glasses filled.

342
00:19:43,837 --> 00:19:44,716
I'll drink first.

343
00:19:53,128 --> 00:19:53,896
(Hi, Barry,)

344
00:19:54,636 --> 00:19:56,557
(thank you for your grace)

345
00:19:56,597 --> 00:19:58,037
(and professionalism)

346
00:19:58,277 --> 00:20:00,757
(in handling Zhao Mei's matter.)

347
00:20:01,357 --> 00:20:04,797
(I think it's time we met.)

348
00:20:05,636 --> 00:20:06,312
(No.)

349
00:20:07,517 --> 00:20:09,676
Mr. Li, Ms. Tan seems angry.

350
00:20:11,037 --> 00:20:11,956
That's her issue.

351
00:20:13,357 --> 00:20:15,956
Mr. Li, may I ask you something?

352
00:20:17,597 --> 00:20:19,837
Does this project truly
need three years?

353
00:20:20,996 --> 00:20:22,956
An extra year
means extra consulting fees.

354
00:20:22,956 --> 00:20:24,196
Use your brain.

355
00:20:33,517 --> 00:20:35,476
Hotels operate differently
from other industries.

356
00:20:35,837 --> 00:20:38,077
Each hotel functions independently.

357
00:20:38,077 --> 00:20:39,517
Frontline hotel staff

358
00:20:39,517 --> 00:20:41,357
only care about
their own hotel's performance.

359
00:20:41,357 --> 00:20:43,077
They have zero interest

360
00:20:43,077 --> 00:20:44,236
in corporate structures.

361
00:20:44,236 --> 00:20:45,476
So-called executive shakeups

362
00:20:45,476 --> 00:20:47,317
mean nothing to them.

363
00:20:47,676 --> 00:20:49,956
- Have you no hotels experience?
- Of course, I have hotel experience.

364
00:20:49,956 --> 00:20:50,757
Well...

365
00:20:50,837 --> 00:20:52,916
But circumstances and challenges differ.

366
00:20:53,156 --> 00:20:54,996
We analyze case by case, right?

367
00:20:54,996 --> 00:20:57,156
Exactly, this topic's
too broad for today.

368
00:20:57,156 --> 00:20:58,357
We can't cover it now.

369
00:20:58,517 --> 00:20:59,996
The setting isn't appropriate either.

370
00:21:00,196 --> 00:21:01,636
Let's just enjoy ourselves here.

371
00:21:01,877 --> 00:21:02,916
Open more champagne.

372
00:21:03,676 --> 00:21:04,517
What does that mean?

373
00:21:05,037 --> 00:21:06,156
You have a problem with me?

374
00:21:06,317 --> 00:21:07,317
Think I'm too young

375
00:21:07,317 --> 00:21:08,117
to talk to?

376
00:21:08,117 --> 00:21:09,676
Or that I wouldn't understand,

377
00:21:09,676 --> 00:21:10,436
so just skip it?

378
00:21:10,636 --> 00:21:12,236
Ms. Tan, you're overthinking.

379
00:21:12,236 --> 00:21:14,037
I've seen this countless times.

380
00:21:14,236 --> 00:21:16,037
Those old-timers
under my father pull this.

381
00:21:16,117 --> 00:21:18,277
When cornered, they change the subject.

382
00:21:18,436 --> 00:21:19,676
They just can't out-argue me.

383
00:21:19,676 --> 00:21:21,236
They can't answer my questions.

384
00:21:21,357 --> 00:21:22,916
But I didn't expect you'd fail too.

385
00:21:22,996 --> 00:21:24,557
Aren't you a top consulting firm?

386
00:21:24,956 --> 00:21:27,236
Seems you've got no efficient solutions.

387
00:21:27,236 --> 00:21:28,837
So-called top consulting firm?

388
00:21:28,837 --> 00:21:30,317
Only your prices are top-tier, right?

389
00:21:30,996 --> 00:21:32,236
That's crossing a line.

390
00:21:32,436 --> 00:21:33,352
- Dongming!
- How is that crossing a line?

391
00:21:33,352 --> 00:21:33,896
Dongming,

392
00:21:34,236 --> 00:21:35,476
Ms. Tan, hear me out.

393
00:21:35,476 --> 00:21:38,436
We're here to find common ground.

394
00:21:38,837 --> 00:21:40,037
Why seek common ground?

395
00:21:40,317 --> 00:21:42,757
Our value is identifying
corporate pain points,

396
00:21:42,757 --> 00:21:43,877
and providing solutions.

397
00:21:43,877 --> 00:21:45,436
Not pandering to the intentions

398
00:21:45,436 --> 00:21:47,436
of a spoiled second-generation rich kid

399
00:21:47,436 --> 00:21:48,357
and flattering her.

400
00:21:48,357 --> 00:21:49,436
Then what are we here for?

401
00:21:49,476 --> 00:21:51,156
Who are you calling a spoiled rich kid?

402
00:21:51,156 --> 00:21:52,196
I must be crazy

403
00:21:52,196 --> 00:21:53,797
to I wasted my time seeing you here.

404
00:21:53,797 --> 00:21:55,916
I'm sorry. I can't help you with this.

405
00:21:56,396 --> 00:21:57,996
I wish you success in your reform.

406
00:21:59,757 --> 00:22:00,317
Dongming!

407
00:22:01,037 --> 00:22:01,636
Dongming!

408
00:22:03,476 --> 00:22:04,396
He didn't mean it.

409
00:22:04,396 --> 00:22:05,156
Move!

410
00:22:07,996 --> 00:22:09,757
This Ms. Tan is really too much.

411
00:22:09,956 --> 00:22:11,476
How can she be so arrogant?

412
00:22:11,476 --> 00:22:12,716
I can't even stand to watch.

413
00:22:12,837 --> 00:22:14,196
She really thinks studying abroad

414
00:22:14,196 --> 00:22:15,676
and inheriting a huge company

415
00:22:15,716 --> 00:22:17,236
make her the greatest person.

416
00:22:17,557 --> 00:22:18,236
Really.

417
00:22:18,236 --> 00:22:19,597
Like we're eager for her business.

418
00:22:19,636 --> 00:22:21,196
Who are you including in "we"?

419
00:22:24,077 --> 00:22:25,877
Have you finished the report
for Wan Jialing?

420
00:22:29,156 --> 00:22:30,396
The report isn't finished.

421
00:22:30,396 --> 00:22:32,156
And you dare pick clients and complain?

422
00:22:32,757 --> 00:22:34,716
You have a brain
to think things through.

423
00:22:35,117 --> 00:22:36,037
How stupid.

424
00:22:42,664 --> 00:22:45,032
(Auntie's Beef Offal)
I can't believe you're still into this.

425
00:22:45,196 --> 00:22:46,196
When you like something,

426
00:22:46,517 --> 00:22:47,277
you can't help it.

427
00:22:50,357 --> 00:22:51,676
Hello, your order is ready.

428
00:22:51,797 --> 00:22:52,877
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

429
00:22:53,236 --> 00:22:54,077
Okay, come on.

430
00:22:56,676 --> 00:22:57,676
I really didn't expect

431
00:22:58,557 --> 00:23:00,716
that Wang Shengdong would call Barry.

432
00:23:01,156 --> 00:23:03,117
Do you know how much
he usually hates Barry?

433
00:23:03,436 --> 00:23:05,436
If it weren't
for the China division's performance,

434
00:23:05,636 --> 00:23:07,916
he would've confronted Barry
head-on long ago.

435
00:23:09,156 --> 00:23:10,396
Things are different now.

436
00:23:11,676 --> 00:23:13,996
Barry is solely focused
on getting re-elected.

437
00:23:13,996 --> 00:23:15,277
Before it is confirmed,

438
00:23:15,277 --> 00:23:16,996
he'll cooperate with the Asia-Pacific.

439
00:23:17,797 --> 00:23:20,436
Even if he knows Wang Shengdong
is trying to annoy him,

440
00:23:20,877 --> 00:23:22,196
he has to accept it.

441
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:24,837
So now he seizes every opportunity

442
00:23:25,357 --> 00:23:26,597
to mess with Barry,

443
00:23:27,476 --> 00:23:28,557
knowing it may be his last

444
00:23:28,716 --> 00:23:29,597
if he wins again.

445
00:23:30,357 --> 00:23:32,636
But when it comes to timing,

446
00:23:32,837 --> 00:23:33,757
you're the expert.

447
00:23:34,037 --> 00:23:35,517
How did it occur to you

448
00:23:36,156 --> 00:23:37,517
to use HQ to break the deadlock?

449
00:23:38,636 --> 00:23:40,236
Don't set me up for a fall, okay?

450
00:23:40,236 --> 00:23:41,117
I just got lucky.

451
00:23:41,916 --> 00:23:42,716
You call this luck?

452
00:23:42,716 --> 00:23:44,757
Let me tell you.
This is called intelligence.

453
00:23:47,597 --> 00:23:48,797
This was such a big deal.

454
00:23:49,357 --> 00:23:51,877
Did you not tell your husband at all

455
00:23:52,317 --> 00:23:54,476
because he works in consulting
and you wanted

456
00:23:54,597 --> 00:23:55,557
to avoid a conflict?

457
00:23:55,797 --> 00:23:56,597
No.

458
00:23:58,156 --> 00:24:00,716
Actually, I almost told him.

459
00:24:01,996 --> 00:24:03,436
But I really wasn't confident.

460
00:24:05,077 --> 00:24:05,956
Not about confidence.

461
00:24:06,436 --> 00:24:07,557
You just hadn't decided yet.

462
00:24:08,757 --> 00:24:09,757
It's been two years.

463
00:24:09,757 --> 00:24:10,837
I've never asked you.

464
00:24:11,837 --> 00:24:12,904
Are you happy with him?

465
00:24:14,557 --> 00:24:15,797
What kind of question is that?

466
00:24:16,636 --> 00:24:17,996
We're very happy.

467
00:24:18,317 --> 00:24:19,956
Yes, my question was a bit problematic.

468
00:24:21,476 --> 00:24:22,676
What I meant to ask is,

469
00:24:23,077 --> 00:24:25,636
you weren't someone
who were eager for marriage before.

470
00:24:26,077 --> 00:24:28,236
How did you suddenly decide
to get married?

471
00:24:31,117 --> 00:24:32,236
He understands me very well.

472
00:24:32,837 --> 00:24:33,597
Understands you?

473
00:24:35,436 --> 00:24:36,916
Can you elaborate?

474
00:24:38,797 --> 00:24:39,757
For example,

475
00:24:40,636 --> 00:24:43,597
although I didn't
tell him everything this time,

476
00:24:43,956 --> 00:24:45,597
after his outburst,

477
00:24:45,597 --> 00:24:46,916
he still chose to help me.

478
00:24:47,956 --> 00:24:49,156
Another example...

479
00:24:51,636 --> 00:24:52,436
It's this late.

480
00:24:52,757 --> 00:24:54,357
Anyone else would've checked on me.

481
00:24:54,357 --> 00:24:55,396
But he won't.

482
00:24:56,616 --> 00:24:58,160
(Honey)
Is this it?

483
00:25:02,236 --> 00:25:03,196
Answer it.

484
00:25:03,196 --> 00:25:04,597
He wasn't like this before.

485
00:25:06,248 --> 00:25:06,809
Hello?

486
00:25:09,236 --> 00:25:10,597
We're at Liede Lane.

487
00:25:15,196 --> 00:25:16,396
You want to pick me up?

488
00:25:19,996 --> 00:25:21,357
Okay, bye-bye.

489
00:25:23,236 --> 00:25:24,877
You shouldn't speak in absolutes.

490
00:25:26,037 --> 00:25:27,436
You still don't understand men.

491
00:25:27,956 --> 00:25:29,277
After I leave in a bit,

492
00:25:29,317 --> 00:25:30,196
he'll tell you,

493
00:25:30,636 --> 00:25:33,077
"Keep your distance with Gao Jiawei."

494
00:25:34,557 --> 00:25:35,156
Impossible.

495
00:25:35,716 --> 00:25:36,557
Don't believe me?

496
00:25:36,877 --> 00:25:38,077
Then let's make a bet.

497
00:25:38,156 --> 00:25:39,277
Bet it is.

498
00:25:41,077 --> 00:25:43,476
The loser treats to beef chow fun.

499
00:25:50,996 --> 00:25:51,496
Hello!

500
00:25:53,156 --> 00:25:55,077
Zhao Mei, this is the big meal you said?

501
00:25:55,716 --> 00:25:56,476
That's on me.

502
00:25:56,837 --> 00:25:58,077
I like this stuff.

503
00:25:59,757 --> 00:26:01,357
He's a guest from afar.

504
00:26:03,797 --> 00:26:04,597
Let's take a photo.

505
00:26:04,877 --> 00:26:05,877
For keepsake.

506
00:26:06,597 --> 00:26:09,317
- You're treating him to this? Come on.
- Yes. Come on. Quick.

507
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:10,636
Come on. For keepsake.

508
00:26:11,916 --> 00:26:12,676
Get in the frame.

509
00:26:12,996 --> 00:26:13,837
Lower your head.

510
00:26:14,277 --> 00:26:15,797
Makes my face look big, right?

511
00:26:16,357 --> 00:26:17,636
Are you embarrassed by me?

512
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:29,064
What are you looking at?

513
00:26:32,436 --> 00:26:34,636
Why did you suddenly want a group photo?

514
00:26:35,277 --> 00:26:36,476
You didn't like it before.

515
00:26:40,877 --> 00:26:43,037
So many people know he once pursued you.

516
00:26:43,236 --> 00:26:45,277
Isn't this to zip their mouths?

517
00:26:45,877 --> 00:26:48,716
To show everyone that I was there
when you two had dinner.

518
00:26:52,597 --> 00:26:54,517
Then what about picking me up?

519
00:26:57,757 --> 00:26:59,037
I wasn't comfortable with it.

520
00:26:59,676 --> 00:27:00,837
Keep your distance with him.

521
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:02,396
Isn't that a bit much?

522
00:27:03,037 --> 00:27:04,517
There's nothing between us.

523
00:27:05,597 --> 00:27:06,837
I'm jealous, okay?

524
00:27:10,077 --> 00:27:12,077
It looks like he's helping you.

525
00:27:12,077 --> 00:27:14,676
But do you know
what his real purpose is?

526
00:27:15,837 --> 00:27:18,196
No matter how high
his position is in the Asia-Pacific,

527
00:27:18,236 --> 00:27:19,597
he's part of the Asia-Pacific.

528
00:27:19,597 --> 00:27:21,077
But you're from the China division.

529
00:27:21,277 --> 00:27:22,916
Your boss is Barry.

530
00:27:25,517 --> 00:27:26,636
I know

531
00:27:27,757 --> 00:27:28,517
what you're saying.

532
00:27:31,317 --> 00:27:34,077
This time, I only seem to have won.

533
00:27:35,476 --> 00:27:37,797
But actually,
I've deeply offended Barry.

534
00:27:37,797 --> 00:27:38,837
Yeah.

535
00:27:39,476 --> 00:27:41,277
You played such a big game.

536
00:27:41,277 --> 00:27:42,196
Should I know earlier,

537
00:27:42,196 --> 00:27:44,236
we wouldn't be so passive now, right?

538
00:27:44,396 --> 00:27:47,716
Can we stop arguing
about what's already happened?

539
00:27:47,716 --> 00:27:48,476
Okay.

540
00:27:48,797 --> 00:27:49,716
I won't say anymore.

541
00:27:57,557 --> 00:27:58,476
In the next few days,

542
00:27:59,557 --> 00:28:01,996
I'll try to arrange
another meeting with Barry.

543
00:28:03,156 --> 00:28:04,196
Apologize to him.

544
00:28:06,117 --> 00:28:06,837
No apology.

545
00:28:06,837 --> 00:28:08,077
I said I'm not apologizing.

546
00:28:08,077 --> 00:28:08,877
I'd rather resign.

547
00:28:08,877 --> 00:28:10,277
What would I become if I apologize?

548
00:28:10,676 --> 00:28:11,277
No apology.

549
00:28:12,916 --> 00:28:15,117
Fine. No apology.

550
00:28:23,557 --> 00:28:26,636
Is it for that project with our company?

551
00:28:29,396 --> 00:28:30,196
Let me tell you.

552
00:28:31,037 --> 00:28:33,196
Now might not be the best time to sign.

553
00:28:33,757 --> 00:28:34,517
What do you mean?

554
00:28:35,156 --> 00:28:37,597
Gao Jiawei is the internal auditor
sent by the Asia-Pacific.

555
00:28:38,357 --> 00:28:39,117
Internal audit?

556
00:28:40,156 --> 00:28:42,716
So now, whether it's a new contract

557
00:28:43,077 --> 00:28:44,837
or a contract being processed,

558
00:28:44,837 --> 00:28:46,597
it all has to go through him.

559
00:28:47,077 --> 00:28:48,117
With so much business,

560
00:28:48,317 --> 00:28:49,716
how could there not be flaws?

561
00:28:53,357 --> 00:28:55,837
They're targeting Barry?

562
00:28:57,396 --> 00:28:58,312
Exactly.

563
00:29:02,676 --> 00:29:05,757
Can you talk to Gao Jiawei for me?

564
00:29:06,396 --> 00:29:09,037
If our company's contract reaches him,

565
00:29:09,396 --> 00:29:10,877
please ask him to go easy on it.

566
00:29:13,396 --> 00:29:14,837
It's really tough.

567
00:29:14,996 --> 00:29:16,357
Fan is putting pressure on me.

568
00:29:17,117 --> 00:29:18,317
Your company's project

569
00:29:18,317 --> 00:29:20,117
is very important to me

570
00:29:20,117 --> 00:29:21,396
and also to our company.

571
00:29:25,597 --> 00:29:26,597
I'll try.

572
00:29:28,716 --> 00:29:29,716
You're the best.

573
00:29:34,396 --> 00:29:35,877
I'll get some sleep. I'm tired.

574
00:29:43,396 --> 00:29:46,277
(Now I know how to deal with Barry.)

575
00:29:55,428 --> 00:29:58,317
(Old friends gathering)

576
00:30:06,903 --> 00:30:08,488
(Barry liked it)

577
00:31:00,317 --> 00:31:01,196
Miss Qiao?

578
00:31:01,797 --> 00:31:02,476
What's wrong?

579
00:31:03,037 --> 00:31:04,117
Did you sprain your ankle?

580
00:31:28,557 --> 00:31:29,396
Thank you.

581
00:31:30,837 --> 00:31:31,432
Your bag.

582
00:31:32,757 --> 00:31:33,317
Thanks.

583
00:31:47,557 --> 00:31:48,877
It is membership-based here.

584
00:31:49,117 --> 00:31:51,517
It offers different dishes
for different solar terms.

585
00:31:51,597 --> 00:31:54,196
So every time you come,
you'll see a different menu.

586
00:31:55,916 --> 00:31:57,676
Dongming, I didn't expect

587
00:31:57,877 --> 00:31:59,877
that you're good friends with...
Who is that?

588
00:32:00,077 --> 00:32:00,837
Gao Jiawei.

589
00:32:00,837 --> 00:32:01,877
Gao Jiawei, yeah.

590
00:32:02,156 --> 00:32:04,476
I didn't know you guys
such good friends.

591
00:32:05,396 --> 00:32:06,557
We knew each other long ago.

592
00:32:06,996 --> 00:32:08,877
And we've always gotten along well.

593
00:32:09,436 --> 00:32:10,357
So,

594
00:32:11,277 --> 00:32:13,557
you guys get along well
because of your wife?

595
00:32:14,156 --> 00:32:16,357
I heard that he was chasing after her.

596
00:32:20,956 --> 00:32:22,716
Come on. It was a compliment.

597
00:32:23,277 --> 00:32:26,236
I mean your wife
is really an attractive woman.

598
00:32:29,956 --> 00:32:30,956
- Barry.
- What?

599
00:32:31,557 --> 00:32:32,317
Did I say it wrong?

600
00:32:32,797 --> 00:32:33,877
She was a promoter.

601
00:32:34,597 --> 00:32:37,396
And promoters must have nice figure.

602
00:32:37,597 --> 00:32:38,676
Have to be good-looking...

603
00:32:47,797 --> 00:32:48,744
Happy about the food?

604
00:32:49,156 --> 00:32:49,916
Not bad.

605
00:32:58,156 --> 00:32:58,916
Professor Feng.

606
00:32:59,797 --> 00:33:00,716
We're together.

607
00:33:01,384 --> 00:33:02,184
What a coincidence!

608
00:33:02,317 --> 00:33:02,920
Ms. Qi.

609
00:33:03,676 --> 00:33:04,716
It's Professor Feng.

610
00:33:04,716 --> 00:33:05,517
Looking for him?

611
00:33:06,877 --> 00:33:07,797
Barry, go down first.

612
00:33:07,797 --> 00:33:08,636
I'll make a call.

613
00:33:08,956 --> 00:33:09,837
Hailun, see him out.

614
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:10,856
Okay.

615
00:33:13,077 --> 00:33:13,797
See you later.

616
00:33:25,037 --> 00:33:27,277
How long have you
been working for Dongming?

617
00:33:29,077 --> 00:33:29,597
A year.

618
00:33:31,557 --> 00:33:34,357
You're not from Guangzhou, are you?

619
00:33:35,996 --> 00:33:38,757
Right, I'm from Yunxi.

620
00:33:39,476 --> 00:33:40,436
Yunxi Province?

621
00:33:41,277 --> 00:33:42,476
Never heard of it.

622
00:33:43,357 --> 00:33:44,196
It's quite far.

623
00:33:44,877 --> 00:33:47,517
It takes three hours
to fly to Guangzhou.

624
00:33:48,877 --> 00:33:51,396
Then you could
find a boyfriend in Guangzhou.

625
00:33:52,357 --> 00:33:54,396
